  <section id="installation">
    <div class="wrap clearfix">
      <h2 class="no-margin-bottom no-margin-top">Installation</h2>
      <p>Download the source code <a class="yellow-text" href="https://github.com/pmkhoa/jquery-menuOnScroll/archive/v.0.1.0.zip">here</a>, and follow two simple steps as below. That is it!</p>
      <div class="installation-guide-wrapper clearfix">
        <div class="installation-guide">
          <h3>Javascript</h3>
          <p>Include jQuery 1.8+ and the menuOnScroll plugin either in the footer or header of your website.</p>
          <p>You can then initialize the plugin right after the document is ready.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="installation-illustration">
          <pre>
&lt;script src="path/to/jquery.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script src="path/to/jquery.menuOnScroll.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  $(document).ready(function() {
    $("#menu").menuOnScroll();
  });
&lt;/script&gt;
          </pre>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="installation-guide-wrapper clearfix">
        <div class="installation-guide">
