  <section id="options">
    <div class="wrap clearfix">
      <h2 class="no-margin-bottom">Options</h2>
      <p>The plugin requires no extra configuration if you follow the HTML markup above. However, it still offers the flexibility that you can configure to meet your requirements.</p> 
      <div class="option">
        <h3 class="no-margin-bottom">menuActiveClass</h3>
        <p>
          Type: <code>String</code><br/>
          Default: <code>"active"</code>
        </p>
        <p>The class that attaches to the menu item when it's active.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="option">
        <h3 class="no-margin-bottom">menuSelector</h3>
        <p>
          Type: <code>Class Selector</code><br/>
          Default: <code>".menu-item"</code>
        </p>
        <p>The class name of the menu item.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="option">
        <h3 class="no-margin-bottom">headerOffset</h3>
        <p>
          Type: <code>Number</code><br/>
          Default: <code>0</code>
        </p>
        <p>The height of the fixed header</p> 
      </div>

      <div class="option">
        <h3 class="no-margin-bottom">footerOffset</h3>
        <p>
          Type: <code>Number</code><br/>
          Default: <code>0</code>
        </p>
        <p>The offset value of footer (if has one), this is used when you want to notify the position of last menu item from the bottom of the page.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="option">
        <h3 class="no-margin-bottom">scrollOnClickOffset</h3>
        <p>
          Type: <code>Number</code><br/>
          Default: <code>80</code>
        </p>
        <p>The offset value used for scroll to element when the menu item is clicked.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
